column5: I can't stand to watch the leafs loose again and the fiancee is still at work.....so I though I'd post some old pics from the archives...sorry no fish this time....ya I'm bored             Jason
Wow those could all be screen savers and wallpaper. Here's the most memorable encounter I had last year.
Some great pics there Basskicker!  Can you tell me where the 3rd & 4th ones are from?  They kind of look like the Scenic High Falls on the Magpie River outside of Wawa.  Thanks for sharing....  dk

I believe the 3rd and 4th one was taken in N.W.T and Yukon. I have over 500 taken from B.C, Yukon, NWT and Alaska.  I got some really cool pics of some wildlife.....grizzly, buffalo, deer, bald eagle.  Maybe the weekend I'll post a few more if you guys are interested.  Jason
I was really enjoying those pictures untill the snake showed up.LOL

Heres a couple from our trip to Quebec a while ago. Thought it was a log floating till i noticed it moving and we got closer to her lol. Was quite a swim for the bugger.....i was worried he wouldnt make it as ive never seen a bear swim, but in the shots, you can see he hit the ground running lol
just a quick post of a picture from a weekend in early oct. it was a great time with a few friends.. one boat didnt even have a motor I towed it with my boat just so we could get out that day.
Geat pics there guys.  Some very nice scenery shots and some places I'd like to visit ... except that darn snake.  I hate those things.
